## Popout Patterns

### Pop out into a floating window

```json
{
  "type": "interactive",
  "action": "popout",
  "targetvalue": "floating",
  "content": "Pop this guide out into a floating window so you can work in Grafana side-by-side."
}
```

### Dock back into the sidebar

```json
{
  "type": "interactive",
  "action": "popout",
  "targetvalue": "sidebar",
  "content": "Dock the guide back into the sidebar to free up screen space."
}
```

> `targetvalue` MUST be `"sidebar"` or `"floating"` — any other value is rejected by the schema.

---

## Open Guide After Navigate Pattern

Chain to a follow-up guide when the user lands on a new page.

```json
{
  "type": "interactive",
  "action": "navigate",
  "reftarget": "/connections/datasources/new",
  "openGuide": "bundled:add-prometheus-datasource",
  "content": "Go to **Add data source** and pick up the Prometheus guide."
}
```

> Prefer `openGuide` over appending `?doc=` to the URL. The query-string form is back-compat only.

---

## Lazy-Rendered Target Pattern

Targets inside virtualized containers (tables, paginated lists, below-fold dashboard rows) need `lazyRender: true` so the engine scrolls them into view. Always wrap the step in a `guided` block — user-paced detection avoids racing the scroll.

```json
{
  "type": "guided",
  "content": "Open the row for `checkoutservice` (it may be below the fold).",
  "steps": [
    {
      "action": "button",
      "reftarget": "div[data-cy='wb-list-item']:has(p:contains('checkoutservice'))",
      "lazyRender": true,
      "scrollContainer": "div[data-testid='dashboards-table'] .scrollbar-view",
      "description": "Click checkoutservice"
    }
  ]
}
```

